& [LMStudioWorkerReadinessSynthesis:20260624_016] is the bounded readiness synthesis for the LM Studio worker lane
  + [synthesis_subject] is complete six-family LM Studio SOP worker corpus
  + [readiness_disposition] is promote to complete-corpus limited-diverse readiness for scratch-isolated prompt-only non-mutating SOP proposal jobs
  + [ready_surface] is Codex-prepared prompt packets, SOP primer and boot packet, scratch isolation, raw output capture, deterministic validator, Codex review, and proposal-only integration
  + [family_count] is 6
  + [accepted_family_signals] is boundary_delineation, outside_preservation, task_frame_routing, evidence_review, periphery_correlation, and integration_disposition
  + [accepted_score_pattern] is six score-100 strong accepted outputs across six distinct task families
  + [attempt_count] is 17 total attempts across the corpus
  + [retry_pattern] is five families required retry or latch tuning and one family passed on first attempt
  + [observed_strengths] is SOP schema completion, outside preservation after latching, task routing under authority boundary, evidence review without integration overclaim, correlation proposal with hypothesis caution, and integration disposition after validation-status correction
  + [observed_faults] is property operator substitution, hollow placeholder fields, missing required literal terms, non-ASCII output, raw SOP property-prefix loss, validation-status blur, empty outside, and authority-boundary fragility
  + [required_latches] is exact raw SOP node shape, two-space property prefix, property operator is, non-placeholder content, required term bundle, ASCII stability, outside-content latch, validation-status truth latch, negative-inside rule, forbidden-term check, and Codex review
  + [codex_review] is accept the corpus as bounded worker-lane readiness evidence but not as autonomous integration authority
  + [readiness_limit] is this proves a useful local worker lane for small SOP proposal jobs, not broad reasoning competence, project-root safety, mutation authority, hidden-state access, or direct trust
  + [next_gate] is compile a limited worker pilot queue for one real non-mutating SOP proposal job with the full synthesis latch set
  + [outside] is broad LM Studio competence, project-root authority, worker mutation, unsupervised PC control, hidden model state, direct trust, automatic launch, destructive action, credentials, and unrelated dirty files

  = must: use complete-corpus limited-diverse readiness language only for scratch-isolated non-mutating SOP proposal jobs
  = must: require the full latch set before any pilot worker output is accepted
  = must: keep Codex as task selector, launcher, validator, integration authority, file writer, committer, and pusher
  = must: preserve every failed attempt as calibration evidence
  = should: use the next pilot to test usefulness on a real SOP maintenance task rather than another artificial family if the task remains non-mutating for the worker
  - never: treat this synthesis as project-root authority, file mutation authority, or broad model competence

(lm_studio_worker_readiness_synthesis) :ready_surface: /family_evidence and latch_set/ |readiness_outside|
  + [ready_surface] is scratch-isolated prompt-only non-mutating SOP proposal jobs
  + [family_evidence] is six accepted score-100 strong task-family signals
  + [latch_set] is exact raw SOP, required literal terms, outside, ASCII, authority boundary, and Codex review
  + [next_gate] is limited worker pilot queue
  |readiness_outside| broad competence, project-root authority, worker mutation, hidden state, direct trust, unsupervised launch, and unrelated dirty files

/ [LMStudioWorkerTaskCorpus], [TaskFrameLaunchQueue], [CodexValidator] -(Synthesizes)> [complete-corpus limited-diverse readiness], [required_latches], [readiness_outside]
* [accepted_family_signals], [observed_faults], [CodexReview] -(Routes)> [limited_worker_pilot_queue], [outside]
